Package: nmatools
Title: Network Meta-Analysis Tools
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Yuki", "Furukawa", email = "furukawa.y.psy@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Wrapper functions and visualization tools for network
    meta-analysis using the 'netmeta' package. Provides one-stop pipelines
    for running NMA, saving outputs (text, RDS, CSV, league tables), and
    generating trimmed, A4-ready forest plots with automatic subnetwork
    detection and page splitting for large plots. Also includes a Shiny
    GUI ('cinema()') for assessing confidence in NMA results using CINeMA
    (Nikolakopoulou et al. 2020) and ROB-MEN (Chiocchia et al. 2021), and
    a suite of publication-ready visualizations: color-coded league tables,
    forest plots and network graphs colored by CINeMA confidence, Kilim
    plots (multi-outcome summary tables), Vitruvian plots (per-treatment
    polar charts of absolute effects), and minimally / partially
    contextualized evidence-classification tables.
